whippyterm (2.0.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Updates to the plugin system
    - Fixed download/upload so you can't try to start a upload/download while the other is active.
    - Added a menu item to copy the current selection to a send buffer
    - Fixed bug with selections in binary mode
    - Added bookmark import/export
    - Added command line options
    - Auto hide of panels made to work
    - A restart is no longer needed to uninstall a plugin
    - Added upgrade plugin
    - Added a calculate CRC dialog
    - Added a select color button to the color settings
    - Added an option to make portable version
    - Installing a data processor plugin will now enable it
    - Server style IO plugins now start with "SRV_"
    - Added an option to add a carriage return when a line feed is received
    - Added option to do local echo
    - Added the transmit delay to settings
    - Moved the QT6 for GUI
    - Reworked custom connection settings menu work
    - Reworked how manage bookmarks dialog handles custom connection settings
    - Added a plugin API to be able to freeze the display
    - Added marks to data processors plugin API
    - Fixed bug where selection would move if back buffer filled
    - Fixed bug where selection was being cleared when clipboard mode wasn't smart
    - Added new misc type of binary plugins
    - Added a text box to the plugin UI API
    - Added a color picker to the plugin UI API
    - Added a groupbox to the plugin UI API
    - Made settings button work for plugins
    - Added selection colors to settings
    - Added a new find CRC dialog
    - Changed copyright message for generated code
    - Added support for a file requester to the UI API
    - Added quick jump for CTRL-C handling
    - Added user styling/color of the selection
    - Updated send block panel to support hex
    - Fixed bug where binary display doesn't stop the cursor from blinking
    - Added a help button to URI input
    - Changed menu buffers to use send buffers name instead of static text
    - Added a set setting to defaults menu option

 -- Paul Hutchinson <paul@whippyterm.com>  Fri, 26 Sep 2025 00:00:00 +0000
